Renault Appoints Tavares as Automaker’s Operating Chief to Succeed Pelata

-- B y   L a u r e n c e   F r o s t
-- 
2011-05-30T17:22:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/renault-appoints-tavares-as-automaker-s-operating-chief-to-succeed-pelata.html
Renault SA (RNO)  appointed  Carlos Tavares 
to succeed Patrick Pelata as chief operating officer, the
company said in an e-mailed statement today.  Tavares, a senior executive at Renault affiliate Nissan
Motor Co., will assume his new duties by July 1, the Renault
statement said. The development of French production sites will
be “a priority,” the statement added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Laurence Frost at 
 lfrost4@bloomberg.net  